sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant Webhook as Validating Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Controller as Training Operator<br/>Controller
    participant Pods as Training Pods<br/>Master/Worker
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>Metrics Collector
    participant Kubelet as Kubelet<br/>Health Monitor

    Note over User,Pods: Flow 1: Training Job Submission (PyTorchJob Example)

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply -f pytorchjob.yaml<br/>Auth: User credentials
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-pytorchjob<br/>mTLS (API Server)
    Webhook->>Webhook: Validate job spec<br/>(replicas, resources, framework config)
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation response
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event: PyTorchJob ADDED<br/>ServiceAccount token

    Controller->>Controller: Reconcile PyTorchJob<br/>Calculate desired state
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Master Pod<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pods (N replicas)<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Service (Master)<br/>Port: 23456/TCP
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ConfigMap<br/>(Training configuration)

    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Resources created
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update PyTorchJob status<br/>Status: Running

    Note over Pods: Training pods communicate directly
    Pods->>Pods: PyTorch distributed training<br/>Port: 23456/TCP (plaintext)<br/>No encryption

    Pods->>Pods: Gradient synchronization<br/>Framework-specific protocol

    Note over Pods: Training completes
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch Pod status changes
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Pods completed
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update PyTorchJob status<br/>Status: Succeeded

    Note over Prometheus,Kubelet: Flow 2 & 3: Monitoring

    Prometheus->>Controller: GET /metrics<br/>HTTP/8080 (no auth)
    Controller-->>Prometheus: Prometheus metrics<br/>(queue depth, reconciliation latency)

    Kubelet->>Controller: GET /healthz<br/>HTTP/8081
    Controller-->>Kubelet: Health: OK
    Kubelet->>Controller: GET /readyz<br/>HTTP/8081
    Controller-->>Kubelet: Ready: OK
